Introduction

TEAPARTY was a three-member fictional project girl group that was created for the KBS2 drama "Imitation".

According to the drama's plot, the group consists of three members under JH Entertainment: Maha (played by actress Jung Jiso), Hyunji (portrayed by former IOI and PRISTIN member Nayoung), and Ria (played by soloist Minseo).

To tease the drama and add a touch of reality, SNS accounts were opened for the group, notably a Twitter account on April 5, 2021, and an Instagram account on April 8. A poster spoiler was also revealed on April 12, followed by an official group poster posted the next day, on April 13, teasing the date May 7, 2021.

TEAPARTY first debuted on May 8, 2021 with the name OMEGA III with the digital single "Call Me (8282119)", but disbanded on the same day because of their pre-debut member scandal.

They redebuted with the name TEAPARTY on May 21, 2021 with the release of the single "Show Me". The group eventually disbanded with the end of the drama and the last release titled "Your Sign", sang along SHAX, SPARKLING, and LA LIMA.
